{
    "text": "sometimes simple is just bestttt! I always talk about how I prep a higher protein sweet treat to stash in my freezer for the week. This makes grabbing a healthier option super easy, you don\u2019t even have to think about it. & being sure to include healthy fats & protein in your sweet treats, is important in keeping you satiated & balancing blood sugar \ud83d\ude4f   This cookie dough bark is vegan, requires no baking, & takes like 5 mins to make!  \u20221/2 cup of your fave protein (i used @macr0mike salted caramel - I have a discount in my bio \ud83e\udd0d) \u20221/2 cup oat flour (you can sub almond flour but you may need to use closer to 3/4 cup) \u20221/4 cup melted coconut oil \u20221/4 cup maple syrup \u20221/2 tsp vanilla + pinch of sea salt \u2022handful of cacao nibs (full of antioxidants! Can also sub choc chips) \u20221 cup chocolate chips  Mix together the cookie dough ingredients. Spread onto a lined baking sheet. Melt the chocolate. Pour over top. Sprinkle with sea salt. Place in the freezer for 2-4 hours until completely firm before breaking into pieces. Store in an air right container in the freezer!  #cookiedough #proteincookiedough #highprotein #highproteinsnack #healthysnacks #healthytreats #vegandessert #vegancookiedough #healthysnackideas",
